description:
Use this function if you are asked to open a file. Input: a file path. Output: an object describing the result of the operation.

Return value:
{
"role": "tool", // Required constant field
"status": "success" | "error",
"error_message": "string | null" // Error details if status = 'error'
}

Example function call parameter: { "path": "/home/user/document.txt" }

Example successful response:
{
"role": "tool",
"status": "success",
"error_message": null
}

Example error response:
{
"role": "tool",
"status": "error",
"error_message": "File not found."
}
